This optic is in excellent condition, with only a pair of tiny silver nicks on the protective hood which seperate it from looking new.

If you are unfamiliar with this optic, it is a very sturdy, reliable, fast, and effective holographic red dot sight. It features a 1 MOA dot inside a 65 MOA circle, meaning the dot is one inch wide at 100 meters. It is adjustable for several brightness setttings. What's best about this optic that seperates it from Wal-Mart specials is that it is very sturdy. Eotech's are commonly purchased by servicemembers for use on their duty rifles overseas, because they are sturdy, reliable, and very fast on target. 380 and a pick-up in the Stillwater area please. Thank you for your time.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Antinque Remington Model 51 .380 Pistol, Collector's Item!
postcontent:
Hello, I have a very rare, antique Remington Model 51 semi-automatic pistol in .380 caliber.  It has been in my family for many years but, due to some financial circumstances, I find myself forced to sell.  I'm not an expert in such matters, but I'd rate the gun approx. 85% in finish and 95% in function (I've only had it to the range a small handful of times in 10 years and have had three failure-to-eject using cheap ball ammo).  There is some bluing wear shown on the outside of the gun on the slide, but overall it's in fantastic shape for its age-a rebluing or restoration specialist could definitely make it perfect.   It is being sold with one original magazine.

Below is a link containing a lot of information on the particular model (including fun facts like General Patton used to carry one in WWII).  As per the standards described on the site, the gun was manufactured between 1918-1921 and would make an excellent piece for a collector.  The same model listed on Gunbroker without reserves are priced between $650-$1100, but I am asking $600 to hopefully facilitate a quick sale and not a lot of lowballing.  I would be willing to entertain a partial trade for a subcompact in .380 or 9mm (Ruger LCP, Kel-Tec, etc) but I will need $300 cash at minimum in addition.  I know there are some people out there that like to email and offer 50% of the asking price-- if this is you, please save both of us the trouble and don't do it.  I do have some things I need to take care of, but I will not just give the gun away.

Please don't hesitate to email me with any questions, specific picture requests, etc.  If, for some reason, I cannot get the pictures to load on the ad I'll be happy to email them to you.

Thanks a lot!
